The paper deals with reasoning in a description logic language (SROEL-R-T) that underlies the OWL EL ontology language, which is commonly used in artificial intelligence applications. The use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) is also a common technique in AI. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with minimal model semantics, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). The use of knowledge bases and instance checking suggests that the paper may also be relevant to databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of answer set preferences, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and constraint programming (cs.CC).
